The paper deals with person Re-Identification (ReID) using end-to-end CNN learning, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as feature extraction, image super-resolution, and attention mechanisms. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as training a fully convolutional auto-encoder and dual-attention block, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed method, which indicates the use of techniques such as regularization and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the use of feature extraction and attention mechanisms, which are common in artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image retrieval, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category.
